  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">REPAM: interconnecting people and organisations in the Brazilian Amazon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">REPAM&#x2019;s project goal is to defend the rights of the poorest and most marginalized populations and to protect the Amazon rainforest. Strengthening the presence of the Catholic Church and its social pastoral work, promoting integral ecology and working towards implementing the Amazon Synodal assembly&apos;s recommendations is REPAM&apos; overall aims. The environment and communities have been under growing threat of deforestation, contamination from mining activities, expansion of agribusiness and impacts of mega infrastructure projects. Human and drug trafficking and migration have increased violence against indigenous groups, landless people and the missionaries/socio-pastoral staffs working with them. Project expected outcomes are strengthened Catholic socio pastoral work providing support to remote Amazonian communities to protect their rights, livelihoods, and the rainforest. REPAM&#x2019;s project also aims to work on critical socio-environmental conflicts involving indigenous and rural traditional communities and building an active volunteer support base around REPAM Local committees in Dioceses of the Amazon. The main beneficiaries are poor and vulnerable communities in rural and urban areas, quilombolas, indigenous groups and socio pastoral workers.</narrative>
  </description>
